sect1.para:
The polyder function returns the polynomial coefficients resulting from differentiation of polynomial p. The syntax for its use is either  pder = polyder(p)
 for the derivitave of polynomial p, or  convp1p2der = polyder(p1,p2)
 for the derivitave of polynomial conv(p1,p2), or still  [nder,dder] = polyder(n,d)
 for the derivative of polynomial n/d (nder is the numerator and dder is the denominator). In all cases the polynomial coefficients are assumed to be in decreasing degree. Contributed by Paulo Xavier Candeias under GPL
